---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
---

<Layout title="Clinical Evaluation">

<Navbar />

<section class="hero">

<div class="container">

<span class="badge">
Clinical Evaluation (CER)
</span>

<h1>Clinical Evaluation for Medical Devices</h1>

<p>

Clinical Evaluation is a systematic and planned process used to
demonstrate that a medical device is safe, performs as intended and
provides clinical benefits throughout its life cycle.

It is one of the most important regulatory requirements under
EU MDR 2017/745 and is also expected during global regulatory
submissions.

</p>

<div class="buttons">

<a href="/learn/risk-management" class="secondary">
← Previous
</a>

<a href="/learn/post-market-surveillance" class="primary">
Next →
</a>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>What is Clinical Evaluation?</h2>

<p>

Clinical Evaluation is the assessment and analysis of clinical data
to verify the safety, performance and clinical benefits of a medical
device.

The final output of this process is called the
<strong>Clinical Evaluation Report (CER).</strong>

Manufacturers use clinical evidence collected from literature,
clinical investigations, post-market surveillance and equivalent
devices to support regulatory approval.

</p>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Objectives of Clinical Evaluation</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>Patient Safety</h3>

<p>

Demonstrate that the device is safe for its intended users.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Clinical Performance</h3>

<p>

Show that the device performs according to its intended purpose.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Benefit-Risk Assessment</h3>

<p>

Verify that the clinical benefits outweigh the residual risks.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Regulatory Compliance</h3>

<p>

Meet EU MDR, ISO 14155 and global regulatory requirements.

</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Sources of Clinical Data</h2>

<table>

<tr>

<th>Source</th>

<th>Description</th>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Clinical Investigation</td>

<td>Prospective clinical studies performed on the device.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Scientific Literature</td>

<td>Published peer-reviewed articles and journals.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Equivalent Devices</td>

<td>Clinical data from similar legally marketed devices.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Post Market Surveillance</td>

<td>Complaint data, vigilance reports and field experience.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>PMCF</td>

<td>Post Market Clinical Follow-up activities.</td>

</tr>

</table>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Clinical Evaluation Process</h2>

<div class="timeline">

<div class="step">Clinical Evaluation Plan</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="step">Literature Search</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="step">Clinical Data Collection</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="step">Data Appraisal</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="step">Clinical Analysis</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="step">Benefit-Risk Evaluation</div>

<div class="arrow">→</div>

<div class="step">Clinical Evaluation Report</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>
<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Regulatory Requirements</h2>

<table>

<tr>

<th>Regulation / Standard</th>

<th>Purpose</th>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>EU MDR 2017/745 Article 61</td>

<td>Clinical Evaluation requirements for Medical Devices.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>MEDDEV 2.7.1 Rev.4</td>

<td>Guidance for Clinical Evaluation methodology.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>ISO 14155</td>

<td>Good Clinical Practice for Clinical Investigations.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>ISO 14971</td>

<td>Risk Management linked with Clinical Evidence.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>ISO 13485</td>

<td>Quality Management System requirements.</td>

</tr>

</table>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Literature Search Strategy</h2>

<p>

A systematic literature review is performed to identify published
clinical evidence related to the medical device or equivalent devices.

The search should be objective, reproducible and well documented.

</p>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>Common Databases</h3>

<ul>

<li>PubMed</li>

<li>Google Scholar</li>

<li>Scopus</li>

<li>Embase</li>

<li>Cochrane Library</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Search Keywords</h3>

<ul>

<li>Device Name</li>

<li>Intended Use</li>

<li>Clinical Performance</li>

<li>Safety</li>

<li>Complications</li>

<li>Revision Surgery</li>

</ul>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Device Equivalence</h2>

<p>

Manufacturers may use clinical data from an equivalent device when
appropriate justification is provided.

Equivalence should be demonstrated in three areas.

</p>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>Technical Equivalence</h3>

<p>

Materials, design, specifications, operating principles and
manufacturing methods should be comparable.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Biological Equivalence</h3>

<p>

Similar materials, tissue contact, biological safety and
biocompatibility characteristics.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Clinical Equivalence</h3>

<p>

Same intended purpose, patient population, anatomical location
and clinical performance.

</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Post Market Clinical Follow-up (PMCF)</h2>

<p>

PMCF is a continuous process used to collect and evaluate clinical
data after the device has been placed on the market.

It confirms long-term safety, performance and identifies new risks.

</p>

<table>

<tr>

<th>PMCF Activity</th>

<th>Purpose</th>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Clinical Follow-up Study</td>

<td>Collect long-term clinical evidence.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>User Surveys</td>

<td>Gather physician and hospital feedback.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Registry Data</td>

<td>Monitor device performance.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>PMS Reports</td>

<td>Evaluate complaints and adverse events.</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Scientific Literature</td>

<td>Identify emerging clinical evidence.</td>

</tr>

</table>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Typical Clinical Evaluation Report (CER) Structure</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<ul>

<li>Clinical Evaluation Plan</li>

<li>Device Description</li>

<li>Intended Purpose</li>

<li>State of the Art</li>

<li>Clinical Background</li>

<li>Literature Search Strategy</li>

<li>Clinical Data Appraisal</li>

<li>Benefit-Risk Analysis</li>

<li>Conclusions</li>

<li>PMCF Plan</li>

</ul>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Supporting Documents</h3>

<ul>

<li>Risk Management File</li>

<li>Biocompatibility Reports</li>

<li>Sterilization Validation</li>

<li>Mechanical Testing</li>

<li>Usability Engineering</li>

<li>PMS Reports</li>

<li>IFU</li>

<li>Technical Documentation</li>

</ul>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Orthopedic Implant Example</h2>

<table>

<tr>

<th>Clinical Question</th>

<th>Evidence</th>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Is the implant safe?</td>

<td>Clinical Studies + PMS Data</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Does it improve mobility?</td>

<td>Published Literature</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>What are the complications?</td>

<td>Revision Registry & Literature</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>What is implant survival?</td>

<td>Long-term Follow-up Studies</td>

</tr>

<tr>

<td>Benefit vs Risk</td>

<td>CER Conclusion</td>

</tr>

</table>

</div>

</section>
<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Hierarchy of Clinical Evidence</h2>

<p>

Not all clinical evidence has the same strength. Regulatory authorities
prefer high-quality clinical evidence when evaluating the safety and
performance of a medical device.

</p>

<table>

<tr>
<th>Evidence Level</th>
<th>Examples</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Highest</td>
<td>Randomized Controlled Trials (RCTs)</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>High</td>
<td>Prospective Clinical Studies</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Moderate</td>
<td>Registry Data & Cohort Studies</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Moderate</td>
<td>Case-Control Studies</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Low</td>
<td>Case Reports & Expert Opinions</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>Supporting</td>
<td>Post Market Surveillance Data</td>
</tr>

</table>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Clinical Evaluation Case Study</h2>

<div class="card">

<h3>Total Hip Replacement Implant</h3>

<p>

A manufacturer develops a cementless total hip implant intended for
patients suffering from osteoarthritis.

The Clinical Evaluation includes:

</p>

<ul>

<li>Published literature on equivalent hip implants</li>

<li>Mechanical testing results</li>

<li>Biocompatibility reports</li>

<li>Sterilization validation reports</li>

<li>Risk Management File (ISO 14971)</li>

<li>Post Market Surveillance data</li>

<li>Clinical follow-up information</li>

</ul>

<p>

After reviewing all available clinical evidence, the manufacturer
demonstrates that the implant is safe, performs as intended and that
its clinical benefits outweigh the identified residual risks.

</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Common Audit Questions</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>Question 1</h3>

<p>

What clinical evidence supports the safety of the device?

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Question 2</h3>

<p>

How was the literature search performed and documented?

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Question 3</h3>

<p>

How was device equivalence established?

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Question 4</h3>

<p>

How are PMCF activities planned?

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Question 5</h3>

<p>

How often is the Clinical Evaluation Report updated?

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Question 6</h3>

<p>

How is Risk Management linked to Clinical Evaluation?

</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

<section>

<div class="container">

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="grid">

<div class="card">

<h3>What is a CER?</h3>

<p>

CER stands for Clinical Evaluation Report. It summarizes all available
clinical evidence supporting the safety and performance of a medical
device.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Is CER mandatory?</h3>

<p>

Yes. Under EU MDR 2017/745, Clinical Evaluation is mandatory for all
medical devices.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>What is PMCF?</h3>

<p>

Post Market Clinical Follow-up is the continuous collection of clinical
data after commercialization.

</p>

</div>

<div class="card">

<h3>Can literature alone be sufficient?</h3>

<p>

For some well-established devices it may contribute significantly, but
manufacturers should justify that the available evidence is sufficient
for the intended purpose and applicable regulations.

</p>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</section>

